modules.description: This module represents files with named content, providing constructors to create files from strings, file paths, or input channels. It supports operations to access a file’s name and content, enabling precise control over how files are uploaded to the MOSS service. Concrete use cases include creating in-memory files from strings, reading files from disk using their path, and handling streaming content via custom input channels.

This module implements a client for submitting code files to the MOSS plagiarism detection service. It supports specifying the programming language, base files, and submission options such as user ID and experimental mode. The main operations include creating and managing files via the `File` submodule and submitting them to MOSS to obtain a detection result URI. Concrete use cases include automating plagiarism checks for programming assignments in courses or code repositories.
